{
  "texts": [
    "Each barcode is designed to emit fluorescence (be \"on\") in exactly k rounds, each time in a single fluorescent channel and stay \"off\" in other rounds.",
    "We concatenate the rounds and channels and represent the barcodes as 3n-dimensional vectors.",
    "In other words, barcode i is represented by vector x i in which 1's are placed where \"on\" signal is expected, and 0's everywhere else.",
    "The codebook matrix X (3nxN) is then defined as X = ½x 1, x 2,:::, x N, where N is the total number of barcodes.",
    "In the same way, for every pixel we concatenate the fluorescent intensity values (scaled between 0 and 1) to create a 3n-dimensional vector y."
  ]
}